Chilean Stocks: CFR Pharmaceuticals, Sigdo Koppers, Socovesa

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-23T20:12:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/chilean-stocks-cfr-pharmaceuticals-sigdo-koppers-socovesa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 1.2 percent to 4,162.52.  CFR Pharmaceuticals SA (CFR CC) increased 2.5 percent to
117.91 pesos. The Chilean drug developer posted second-quarter
net income of $24.3 million, up from $20.5 million a year
earlier, according to a filing on the website of  Chile ’s
securities regulator. Revenue in the period rose 36 percent to
$120 million.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   gained 8.6 percent to 886 pesos.
The Chilean holding company said it agreed to buy  Belgium ’s
Magotteaux SA for $790 million to expand its services to the
 mining industry . The purchase includes 12 production plants in
10 countries, Santiago-based Sigdo Koppers said in a statement
distributed by e-mail.  Socovesa SA (SOCOVESA)  , a builder and real-estate
developer, increased 1.1 percent to 218.33 pesos. Chile’s
central bank may cut rates if a global slowdown reduces
commodity prices and damps growth in the world’s biggest copper
producer, where domestic demand is showing signs of slowing,
bank President Jose De Gregorio said at the Bloomberg Chile
Economic Summit in Santiago today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
